import Mathlib

open Set

/-!
# Structure of the Ω-subgroup generated by a set

If G is an Ω-group and X is a nonempty subset, then the Ω-subgroup X^Ω generated
by X consists of all elements of the form

  (x_{i₁}^{ε₁})^{ω₁} · (x_{i₂}^{ε₂})^{ω₂} · ... · (x_{i_r}^{ε_r})^{ω_r}

where x_i ∈ X, ε_i = ±1, r ≥ 0, and each ω_i is a finite sequence of operators
from Ω applied successively.

