- `MulDistribMulAction`: `GroupAction/Defs.lean`
- `Subgroup`: `Algebra/Group/Subgroup/Defs.lean`
- `Subgroup.closure`: `Algebra/Group/Subgroup/Lattice.lean`
-/

universe u v

/-! ### Ω-subgroup definition -/

variable {Ω : Type v} [Monoid Ω] {G : Type u} [Group G] [MulDistribMulAction Ω G]

/-- An Ω-subgroup of an Ω-group G is a subgroup H that is Ω-admissible, i.e.,
for every h ∈ H and ω ∈ Ω, we have ω • h ∈ H. -/
